meVE.Stichera01.mode = miscellanea_en_US_goadedes.misc.Mode6
meVE.Stichera01.greekmelody = he.a.m6_en_US_goadedes.heAU.OlinApothemenoi.greekname
meVE.Stichera01.melody = he.a.m6_en_US_goadedes.heAU.OlinApothemenoi.name
meVE.Stichera01.incipit = "Contemplation being found…"
meVE.Stichera01.text = "Contemplation being reached by means of virtue in action, * you set contemplation as * the goal of your actions done for the love of God. * Hence you asked Christ the show * you the Father’s glory * which is truly indescribable. * Indeed, O glorious * Philip, every rational being longs * for God who had created it. * Forthwith You were granted to see the One * for whom you were longing, accepting as His stamp His only Son. * And now implore Him with confidence * for our souls unceasingly."

meVE.Stichera02.mode = miscellanea_en_US_goadedes.misc.Mode6
meVE.Stichera02.melody = he.a.m6_en_US_goadedes.heAU.OlinApothemenoi.name
meVE.Stichera02.incipit = "You continually had…"
meVE.Stichera02.text = "You continually had divine ascents, O Apostle, * much like Moses long before, * and you likewise longed to have a vision of God. * You indeed clearly saw * His authentic image * and accepted His identity. * For since the essence of the Son and the Father is known as one, * the Son is the immediate * knowledge of the Father, revealing Him; * and in every manner the oneness and identity is shown, * the kingdom, power and glory, and worship of the one true God."

meVE.Stichera03.mode = miscellanea_en_US_goadedes.misc.Mode6
meVE.Stichera03.melody = he.a.m6_en_US_goadedes.heAU.OlinApothemenoi.name
meVE.Stichera03.incipit = "You became the instrument …"
meVE.Stichera03.text = "You became the instrument of God the all-holy Spirit, * who inspired and guided you * to proclaim the word of God, as if strumming you. * In the world echoing the supernal Gospel * of the Savior, with the fiery tongue * that animated you, you incinerated the flammable * deception of idolatry, * which withered like grass that is burned in fire. * O Apostle Philip, you preached throughout the world that Jesus Christ * is Lord of all and the Son of God, the King of the universe."

meVE.SticGlory.poet = poets_en_US_goadedes.po.Vyzantos
meVE.SticGlory.mode = miscellanea_en_US_goadedes.misc.Mode6
meVE.SticGlory.melody = ""
meVE.SticGlory.incipit = "You shone like a star…"
meVE.SticGlory.text = "You shone like a star throughout the world, O Philip, ignited by the flashes coming from the great light. You had sought the Father of lights and found Him in the Son; for the light is found in the light, and He is the exact seal revealing the original. Implore Him, O Apostle, to preserve us who have been sealed in His divine blood."

meVE.SticTheotokion.mode = miscellanea_en_US_goadedes.misc.Mode6
meVE.SticTheotokion.melody = ""
meVE.SticTheotokion.incipit = oc.m6.d1_en_US_goadedes.ocVE.SticTheotokion.incipit
meVE.SticTheotokion.text = oc.m6.d1_en_US_goadedes.ocVE.SticTheotokion.text

meVE.Aposticha1.mode = miscellanea_en_US_goadedes.misc.Mode8
meVE.Aposticha1.greekmelody = he.a.m8_en_US_goadedes.heAU.OTouParadoxou.greekname
meVE.Aposticha1.melody = he.a.m8_en_US_goadedes.heAU.OTouParadoxou.name
meVE.Aposticha1.incipit = "What an amazing phenomenon…"
meVE.Aposticha1.text = "What an amazing phenomenon! He who had previously * used a net, as a fisherman, * was chosen by God to be an Apostle and fisher of men. * He hauled in Gentiles with words instead of nets, * and caught the world with the Cross instead of hooks. * Great was the human catch * that through holy baptism he brought to Christ. * And today we celebrate his sacred memory."

meVE.Aposticha2.mode = miscellanea_en_US_goadedes.misc.Mode8
meVE.Aposticha2.melody = he.a.m8_en_US_goadedes.heAU.OTouParadoxou.name
meVE.Aposticha2.incipit = "What an amazing accomplishment…"
meVE.Aposticha2.text = "What an amazing accomplishment! Philip was sent out by God * as a sheep in the midst of wolves, * and, behold, into the world the Apostle went fearlessly. * Converting beasts into lambs when they believed, * by divine grace he transformed society. * Great and ineffable * are the works and miracles he did by faith. * Through his prayers save our souls, only compassionate Lord."

meVE.Aposticha3.mode = miscellanea_en_US_goadedes.misc.Mode8
meVE.Aposticha3.melody = he.a.m8_en_US_goadedes.heAU.OTouParadoxou.name
meVE.Aposticha3.incipit = "What an amazing phenomenon…"
meVE.Aposticha3.text = "What an amazing phenomenon! Apostle Philip became * like a well gushing forth with life * for believers, which they draw with the bucket of wisdom divine. * Like streams of water his doctrines flow from it; * his signs and wonders refresh us like a drink. * Great and sensational * are the mighty deeds that God performed through him, * whose annual memory we celebrate with faith."

meVE.AposGlory.poet = poets_en_US_goadedes.po.Vyzantiou
meVE.AposGlory.mode = miscellanea_en_US_goadedes.misc.Mode2
meVE.AposGlory.melody = ""
meVE.AposGlory.incipit = "You left behind…"
meVE.AposGlory.text = "You left behind what was yours on earth, and you followed Christ. When He sealed you by breathing the Holy Spirit into you, He sent you to the lost Gentiles, to bring the people back to the light of the knowledge of God, O Apostle Philip. When you completed the contest of your divine love, being tortured in many ways, you gave up your soul to God. Entreat Him, O all-blessed Saint, to grant us the great mercy."

